            <Text fill="WHITE" layoutX="23.0" layoutY="73.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="In short, GNU is a bunch of tools, compilers, Command Line Utilities, and other software: All the necessary tools to make up an Operating System.&#10;&#10;The Kernel talks between GNU and the hardware. The kernel can be used on different operating systems too, such as many versions of Android are running the Linux Kernel. &#10;&#10;There are also multiple versions of operating systems, GNU and Linux make up the basic tools required to make the operating system but it's not the full and final product, lots of other things need to be completed and that's why there are so many versions of GNU/Linux." wrappingWidth="711.0">
